definition: birthday
to be born/to give birth/life/to grow/raw/uncooked/student
5th earthly branch: 7-9 a.m., 3rd solar month (5th April-4th May), year of the Dragon/ancient Chinese compass point: 120°
one's birth data for astrological purposes, combined from year, month, day, hour, heavenly trunk and earthly branch

sentences.english: And look upon my self and curse my fate.

sentences.english: Mine is Topaz which is the birthstone of November.
sentences.chinese: 我出生於十一月，所以我的生辰石是託帕石。

sentences.english: I wrote my birth time on a piece of paper and handed it to the fortune-teller.

sentences.english: A chart is as map to search self and a beginning to fulfill a mission.

sentences.english: There are different opinions on Confucious exact birthday in the historical records.

sentences.english: I'm bound to come your birthday party tomorrow night.

sentences.english: In the ancient times, Kongzi’s birthday was regarded as a Teachers'Day.

sentences.english: My birthday is November the eight.
